√âtudions pour une s√©rie quelconque (downscal√©e (x81)) la correlation temporelle.

for (decal in -1:3){
  if(decal>=0){
    points_pr<-((decal+1):n)
    points_deb<-(1:(n-decal))
  }
  else{
    points_deb<-((1-decal):n)
    points_pr<-(1:(n+decal))
  }
  #layout(matrix(1:2,1,2))
plot((pr_series[points_pr,2]-pr_series[points_pr,1])/pr_series[points_pr,1],(simu_deb[points_deb,2]-simu_deb[points_deb,1])/simu_deb[points_deb,1], main= paste("delta Q /delta R dwnsc decal=",decal, sep=""), xlab="delta R", ylab="delta Q", xlim = c(-1,1),ylim=c(-1,1))

for(i in 2:10){
  cat(paste("On commence le calcul des droites de regression pour l'it√©ration ", i, "\n",  sep=""))
  X<-cbind((pr_series[points_pr,i]-pr_series[points_pr,1])/pr_series[points_pr,1],(simu_deb[points_deb,i]-simu_deb[points_deb,1])/simu_deb[points_deb,1])
  par<- projection(c(0.7,0.7,0,0,0,1,0,0))
  fn<-function(Y){
    return(d_fn(Y, X))
  }
  plot(X[,1],X[,2], main= paste("delta Q /delta R dwnsc decal=",decal," deg (x",(2*i-1)^2,")", sep=""), xlab="delta R", ylab="delta Q", xlim = c(-1,2),ylim=c(-1,2.5))
  
  opt<-optimisation(fn, par,1e-4)
  res<-opt$Xmin
  a1<-res[2]/res[1]
  b1<-res[4]-res[3]*a1
  abline(b1,a1,col="red")
  a2<-res[2+4]/res[1+4]
  b2<-res[4+4]-res[3+4]*a2
  abline(b2,a2, col="blue")
  Coeff[,i]<-res
  Min[,i]<-opt$fmin
}

Test de Cramer-von Mises

source(paste(loc,"/codes_utiles/test_stat_Cramer_von_Mises.R",sep=""))
## Warning: package 'goftest' was built under R version 4.0.3
#On applique l'algorithme de Cramer-von Mises
CVM_simu_deb<-function(serie){return(cvm(serie,simu_deb[,1],TRUE))}
CVM_simu_etr<-function(serie){return(cvm(serie,simu_etr[,1],TRUE))}
deb_CVM<-apply(simu_deb, 2, CVM_simu_deb)
etr_CVM<-apply(simu_etr, 2, CVM_simu_etr)
#CVM$T # donne la valeur de la "distance" entre les cdfs
#CVM$pval # p-value du test CvM 
deb_CVM_stat<-matrix(0,1,5)
etr_CVM_stat<-matrix(0,1,5)
for (i in (1:6)){
  deb_CVM_stat[i]<-deb_CVM[[i]]$T
  etr_CVM_stat[i]<-etr_CVM[[i]]$T
  deb_CVM_stat[i+5]<-deb_CVM[[i+5]]$T
  etr_CVM_stat[i+5]<-etr_CVM[[i+5]]$T
}
layout(matrix(1:2,1,2))
deg<-c(1,9,25,49,81, 121)
plot(deg,c(1,7,8,9,10,11), main= "dist CvM d√©bits dwnsc(blue)/ deg(red)", xlab="deg" , ylab="CvM", type="l", col= "red")
lines(deg,deb_CVM_stat[1:6], col="blue")
plot(deg,etr_CVM_stat[1:6], main= "dist CvM etr dwnsc(blue)/ deg(red)", xlab="deg" , ylab="CvM", type="l", col= "blue")
lines(deg,etr_CVM_stat[c(1,7,8,9,10,11)], col="red")

On voit, alors que la distance de CvM √©tait tr√®s grande pour les pr√©cipitations, elle est quasiment nulle pour les d√©bit. C‚Äôest un relativement bon indicateur pour estimer la qualit√© de nos pr√©dictions.
